      "type": "ValidationResult",
      "name": "Mesh convergence study — FDA generic centrifugal blood pump",
      "description": "Grid refinement study performed at base mesh size 0.15 mm (fine), 0.25 mm (medium), and 0.40 mm (coarse). GCI between fine and medium grids was 2.1% for predicted RH, satisfying the MRL 2 discretization requirement. All subsequent validation runs used the 0.15 mm base mesh at the chosen settings.",
      "outcome": "Pass",
      "quantitativeResult": "GCI = 2.1% (fine-to-medium); RH_fine = 0.74"
    },
    {
      "id": "https://uofa.net/synth/validation/gcbp-experimental-comparison-v1",
      "type": "ValidationResult",
      "name": "Experimental hemolysis comparison — 5 operating points",
      "description": "CFD-predicted normalized index of hemolysis (NIH) compared against in-vitro measurements at 5 flow-speed combinations. Simulations executed with C_mu = 0.09 and scalar convergence threshold 1e-5 at the chosen settings. Mean absolute error 8.3%; all predictions within 15% of measurement. RH < 1 satisfied at worst-case operating point (4 L/min, 3500 rpm).",
      "outcome": "Pass",
      "quantitativeResult": "MAE = 8.3%; RH_worst = 0.81 (< 1.0 acceptance criterion)"
    },
    {
      "id": "https://uofa.net/synth/validation/gcbp-sensitivity-cmu-v1",
      "type": "ValidationResult",
      "name": "Turbulence closure sensitivity — C_mu parameter",
      "description": "Sensitivity of NIH predictions to C_mu was evaluated at the nominal value of 0.09 only. The assessment notes that C_mu influences near-wall shear stress and hence hemolysis scalar transport, but a formal range study was deferred. Deployment guidance does not specify a required value or acceptable range for C_mu; operators are expected to use solver defaults, which may differ across CFD platforms.",
      "outcome": "Pass",
      "quantitativeResult": "NIH sensitivity to C_mu not formally bounded; nominal result at C_mu = 0.09 accepted"
    }
  ],
