    "role": "Credibility assessment team",
    "outcome": "Accepted",
    "rationale": "All seven assessed credibility factors meet or exceed required gradation levels for MRL 2. Six factors are not assessed per MRL 2 scoping, consistent with ASME V&V 40-2018 Table 3. Validation results demonstrate RH = 0.81 at worst-case operating point, satisfying the RH < 1 acceptance criterion. The CFD model is accepted as sufficiently credible for the CPB COU. Assessors note that simulation configuration parameters (base mesh size, C_mu, convergence threshold) were used at specific values during validation; the mesh size is documented in the convergence report, but C_mu and the convergence threshold are not formally pinned in a deployment configuration specification or linked settings node. This is considered acceptable at MRL 2 given the supporting experimental comparison, but downstream users should verify solver defaults prior to deployment use.",
